      <source srcset="flap-narrow-dark.png" media="(prefers-color-scheme: dark)">
      <img src="flap-narrow.png" alt="flap-narrow">
    </picture>

    The :class:`Adw.Flap` widget can display its children like a :class:`Gtk.Box` does or
    like a :class:`Gtk.Overlay` does, according to the
    :attr:`Flap.fold-policy` value.

    :class:`Adw.Flap` has at most three children: :attr:`Flap.content`,
    :attr:`Flap.flap` and :attr:`Flap.separator`. Content is the primary
    child, flap is displayed next to it when unfolded, or overlays it when
    folded. Flap can be shown or hidden by changing the
    :attr:`Flap.reveal-flap` value, as well as via swipe gestures if
    :attr:`Flap.swipe-to-open` and/or :attr:`Flap.swipe-to-close` are set
    to ``True``.

