    interface supports adding layouts via ``<child>`` element with the ``type``
    attribute omitted.

    It also supports setting children via ``<child type="ID">``.

    Example of an :class:`Adw.MultiLayoutView` UI definition that can display a secondary
    child as either a sidebar or a bottom sheet.

    .. code-block:: xml

        <object class=":class:`Adw.MultiLayoutView`">
          <child>
            <object class=":class:`Adw.Layout`">
              <property name="name">sidebar</property>
              <property name="content">
                <object class=":class:`Adw.OverlaySplitView`">
                  <property name="sidebar">
                    <object class=":class:`Adw.LayoutSlot`">
                      <property name="id">secondary</property>
                    </object>
                  </property>
                  <property name="content">
                    <object class=":class:`Adw.LayoutSlot`">
                      <property name="id">primary</property>
                    </object>
                  </property>
                </object>
              </property>
            </object>
          </child>
          <child>
            <object class=":class:`Adw.Layout`">
              <property name="name">bottom-sheet</property>
              <property name="content">
                <object class=":class:`Adw.BottomSheet`">
                  <property name="open">True</property>
                  <property name="content">
                    <object class=":class:`Adw.LayoutSlot`">
                      <property name="id">primary</property>
                    </object>
                  </property>
                  <property name="sheet">
                    <object class=":class:`Adw.LayoutSlot`">
                      <property name="id">secondary</property>
                    </object>
                  </property>
                </object>
              </property>
            </object>
          </child>
          <child type="primary">
            <!-- ... -->
          </child>
          <child type="secondary">
            <!-- ... -->
          </child>
        </object>

